Starting Points: 35,000\nExtension into South: At the end of 3rd East game, if 1st place has less than 40,000 points\nLength: East Round Match\nRed Five: 2\nOpen Tanyao: On\nTsumo Loss： On\nWaiting Time: 5+20
\n - 8 Dead Wall tiles;
\n - 2,3,4,5,6,7,8-Man tiles are not used;
\n - “Chii” is not allowed;
\n - “North Wind” can be melded and used as a Kita Dora. Upon calling Kita, the player can draw an extra tile from the Dead Wall.
\n - “Tsumo” after Kita is considered a Dead Wall Draw;
\n - Kita is considered as a call (which disables Ippatsu/Miracle (Non-Dealer)/Nine Terminal Initial Draw/Double Riichi) but does not make Menzenchin invalid;
\n - Players can declare a Ron when others are Kita, but this has no Yaku;
\n - North Wind triplets are not considered as Yaku;

